===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|ilke}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|ilca|}}, conjectured as from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*ilīkaz}}, a compound of {{m|gem-pro|*iz}} and {{m|gem-pro|*-līkaz}} from the noun {{m|gem-pro|*līką||body}}.

The sense of “type”, “kind” is from the application of the phrase ‘{{m|en|of that ilk}}’ to families: the word thus came to mean ‘{{m|en|family}}’.

